title: Help me!

replies.body:
Copy your saves, resourcepacks, server.dat to your desktop from .minecraft.

Then delete everything in your minecraft folder, drag the three files (above) and launch minecraft.
What I did when my minecraft kept crashing.

replies.body:
Try using another version, another profile or change the texture pack.
If you have used McEdit (1.8) on a downloaded world and use 1.7 you will most likely crash after a few mins.
